						description = <"Clinical scoring system used to predict severity of community-acquired pneumonia, measured in 30-day mortality. CRB-65 is an acronym for Confusion, Respiratory rate, Blood pressure and age (over or equal to) 65. It is derived from the CURB-65 score and is the recommended option when blood urea results are not available. Patients scoring one point or higher should be considered for hospital admission.">
